  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: '- SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW:


    1/ The Motherboard: The central
    nervous system. Everything connects here. Ensure your socket type matches your
    CPU.


    2/ The Processor (CPU): The brain of the build. Generates the most
    heat; never forget thermal paste and a cooler.


    3/ Memory (RAM): Short-term
    storage. Higher speeds and dual-channel configurations significantly impact benchmark
    scores.


    4/ Graphics Unit (GPU): The muscle. Responsible for rendering frames.
    Check your PSU wattage before installing high-end cards.


    5/ Power Supply
    (PSU): The heart. Provides steady voltage to all components. Efficiency ratings
    (80 Plus) matter for stability.


    6/ Storage (SSD/HDD): Where the data lives.
    NVMe drives offer the fastest boot times and loading speeds.'
