  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DescriptionUpdater
  generalDescriptionText: {fileID: 908030553}
  detailedDescriptionText: {fileID: 897226270}
  specsText: {fileID: 0}
  defaultGeneralText: Select a component category to learn what it does.
  defaultDetailedText: Select a component to view details.
  defaultSpecsText: 
  categoryDescriptions:
  - category: 0
    description: "- Central Processing Unit (CPU)\r\n\r\nThe CPU is the primary engine
      of the computer, responsible for interpreting and executing most of the commands
      from the computer's hardware and software. \nIt handles all the complex logic
      and mathematical calculations required to keep the system running.\r\n\r\n-Performance
      Impact: High core counts and clock speeds improve multitasking, video rendering,
      and high-frame-rate gaming.\r\n\r\n-Key Specs: \nClock Speed (GHz), Cores,
      Threads, and Socket Type."
  - category: 2
    description: "- Graphics Processing Unit (GPU)\r\n\r\nThe GPU is a specialized
      processor designed to rapidly manipulate and alter memory to accelerate the
      creation of images in a frame buffer intended for output to a display. While
      the CPU handles logic.\nthe GPU handles the heavy lifting of rendering 3D graphics
      and textures.\r\n\r\n-Performance Impact: \nThis is the most critical component
      for gaming resolution, ray tracing, and visual fidelity.\r\n\r\n-Key Specs:\n
      VRAM (GB), Clock Speed, and Power Draw (TDP)."
  - category: 1
    description: "-Random Access Memory (RAM)\r\n\r\nRAM provides a high-speed \"workspace\"
      for the CPU. It temporarily stores the data that the system is actively using
      so it can be accessed almost instantly. \nUnlike storage, RAM is volatile;
      it clears completely when the power is turned off.\r\n\r\n-Performance Impact:
      \nMore RAM allows you to run more programs at once without the system slowing
      down or \"stuttering.\"\r\n\r\n-Key Specs: \nCapacity (GB), Speed (MHz), and
      Latency (CL)."
  - category: 3
    description: "-Motherboard\r\n\r\nThe motherboard is the main printed circuit
      board that connects all components of the computer. It acts as a hub, allowing
      the CPU, RAM, and GPU to communicate with each other. \nIt also determines
      what kind of hardware you can use based on its socket and chipset.\r\n\r\n-Performance
      Impact: \nWhile it doesn't \"speed up\" the PC directly, it dictates your upgrade
      path and features like overclocking support and Port (USB/M.2) availability.\r\n\r\n-Key
      Specs: \nSocket Type, Chipset, and Form Factor (ATX, Micro-ATX, IT/X)."
  - category: 4
    description: "-Storage (SSD & HDD)\r\n\r\nStorage is where all your data\u2014the
      Operating System, games, and files\u2014lives permanently.\r\n\r\n-SSDs (Solid
      State Drives):\n Use flash memory. They are incredibly fast, silent, and durable.
      They make the computer boot in seconds and games load almost instantly.\r\n\r\n-HDDs
      (Hard Disk Drives):\nUse spinning mechanical platters. They are slower and
      louder but offer massive amounts of space for a very low price.\r\n\r\n-Key
      Specs:\n Capacity (GB/TB), Read/Write Speed (MB/s), and Interface (SATA vs.
      NVMe)."
